And on the other hand, RegionAwareEnsemblePlacementPolicy with reorderReadSequenceEnabled works as expected.
Using the following placement
```
bin/pulsar-admin bookies racks-placement                                                              
{
  "default" : {
    "bk1-eu:3181" : {
      "rack" : "eu/1"
    },
    "bk2-eu:3181" : {
      "rack" : "eu/1"
    },
    "bk2-us:3181" : {
      "rack" : "us/1"
    },
    "bk1-us:3181" : {
      "rack" : "us/1"
    },
    "pulsar1-eu:6650" : {
      "rack" : "eu/1"
    },
    "pulsar2-eu:6650" : {
      "rack" : "eu/1"
    },
    "pulsar1-us:6650" : {
      "rack" : "us/1"
    },
    "pulsar2-us:6650" : {
      "rack" : "us/1"
    }
  }
}
```
Consumption from "eu" brokers goes to "eu" bookies as expected

So I propose to add two broker config params:
* `bookkeeperClientRegionawarePolicyEnabled` to activate region aware policy. If set, the value of `bookkeeperClientRackawarePolicyEnabled` will not be used.
* `reorderReadSequenceEnabled`

I'll do the PR if it's OK.

@lovelle 

